# Design System Guardian

This rule enforces consistency with the base design system, accessibility standards, and frontend best practices. Apply these rules to ALL frontend code.

## Rule 1: Always Use Design Tokens

### Colors
- NEVER hardcode color values (hex, rgb, hsl) in component styles.
- ALWAYS use semantic CSS custom properties: `var(--color-bg-primary)`, `var(--color-text-secondary)`, etc.
- Use SEMANTIC tokens (`--color-bg-*`, `--color-text-*`, `--color-fg-*`, `--color-border-*`), not primitives (`--gray-500`, `--brand-600`).
- Exception: Primitive tokens are acceptable ONLY inside `overrides.css` when redefining semantic tokens.

### Spacing
- NEVER hardcode spacing values (margin, padding, gap) as raw pixels or rems.
- ALWAYS use spacing tokens: `var(--spacing-xs)`, `var(--spacing-md)`, `var(--spacing-3xl)`, etc.
- Spacing scale: none(0), xxs(2), xs(4), sm(6), md(8), lg(12), xl(16), 2xl(20), 3xl(24), 4xl(32), 5xl(40), 6xl(48), 7xl(64), 8xl(80), 9xl(96), 10xl(128), 11xl(160).

### Border Radius
- NEVER hardcode border-radius values.
- ALWAYS use radius tokens: `var(--radius-sm)`, `var(--radius-md)`, `var(--radius-full)`, etc.
- Scale: none(0), xxs(2), xs(4), sm(6), md(8), lg(10), xl(12), 2xl(16), 3xl(20), 4xl(24), full(9999).

### Typography
- ALWAYS use typography tokens for font-family, font-size, font-weight, and line-height.
- `var(--font-family-display)` for headings, `var(--font-family-body)` for body text.
- `var(--font-weight-regular)` (400), `--font-weight-medium` (500), `--font-weight-semibold` (600), `--font-weight-bold` (700).
- Font sizes: `var(--font-size-text-sm)`, `var(--font-size-display-lg)`, etc.
- Line heights: `var(--line-height-text-sm)`, `var(--line-height-display-lg)`, etc.

### Shadows
- NEVER hardcode box-shadow values.
- ALWAYS use shadow tokens: `var(--shadow-xs)` through `var(--shadow-3xl)`.
- Elevation guide: xs=inputs, sm=cards, md=tooltips, lg=modals, xl=overlays, 2xl=popovers, 3xl=showcases.

## Rule 2: Dark Mode Compliance

- Every component MUST work in both light and dark mode without additional CSS.
- This happens automatically WHEN you use semantic tokens (`--color-bg-*`, `--color-text-*`, etc.).
- If you hardcode a color, dark mode WILL break. This is why Rule 1 exists.
- If a component needs a color that doesn't exist as a token, add a new semantic token to `overrides.css` with both `:root` and `.dark` values.
- Test by toggling the `.dark` class on the root element.

## Rule 3: Accessibility Standards

### Color Contrast
- Normal text (below 18px/14px bold): minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio (WCAG AA).
- Large text (18px+ or 14px+ bold): minimum 3:1 contrast ratio.
- UI components and graphical objects: minimum 3:1 contrast ratio against adjacent colors.
- The semantic token system is pre-tested for contrast. If you use `--color-text-primary` on `--color-bg-primary`, contrast is guaranteed. If you mix tokens in unusual ways, verify manually.

### Interactive Elements
- All interactive elements (buttons, links, inputs) MUST have visible focus styles.
- Use the focus ring tokens: `--color-focus-ring` (brand) and `--color-focus-ring-error` (error states).
- Focus styles must be visible in both light and dark modes.
- Standard focus style: `outline: 2px solid var(--color-focus-ring); outline-offset: 2px;`
- Never use `outline: none` without providing an alternative visible focus indicator.

### Keyboard Navigation
- All interactive elements must be reachable via Tab key.
- Use semantic HTML elements (`<button>`, `<a>`, `<input>`) instead of `<div>` with click handlers.
- If you must use a non-semantic element, add `tabindex="0"`, `role`, and keyboard event handlers (Enter/Space).
- Dropdown menus and modals must trap focus and support Escape to close.

### ARIA and Semantic HTML
- Use semantic HTML elements first: `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`.
- Add `aria-label` or `aria-labelledby` to navigation landmarks, modals, and form groups.
- Icon-only buttons MUST have `aria-label` describing the action.
- Form inputs MUST have associated `<label>` elements (via `for`/`id` or wrapping).
- Images must have meaningful `alt` text, or `alt=""` for decorative images.
- Use `aria-live="polite"` for dynamic content updates (toasts, alerts, loading states).
- Use `aria-expanded` on toggles/dropdowns, `aria-selected` on tabs, `aria-current="page"` on active nav items.

### Motion and Animation
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`. Wrap animations in:
  ```css
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
    .element { transition: transform 0.2s ease; }
  }
  ```
- Never auto-play animations that flash more than 3 times per second.
- Provide a mechanism to pause/stop any animation that lasts longer than 5 seconds.

### Touch Targets
- Minimum interactive touch target size: 44x44px (WCAG 2.5.5).
- If the visible element is smaller (e.g., a small icon button), use padding or `min-width`/`min-height` to meet the target size.

## Rule 4: File Organization

### Where Files Go
- Base component styles (matching Figma): `styles/base/[component].css`
- Custom project components: `styles/custom/[component].css`
- Base component markup: `components/base/[Component].*`
- Custom component markup: `components/custom/[Component].*`
- Token overrides: `styles/tokens/overrides.css`
- NEVER modify `styles/tokens/base.css` or `styles/tokens/base-components.css`.

### Naming Conventions
- CSS files: `kebab-case.css` (e.g., `dashboard-card.css`)
- Component files: `PascalCase` (e.g., `DashboardCard.tsx`)
- CSS classes: `kebab-case` with BEM (e.g., `.dashboard-card`, `.dashboard-card__title`, `.dashboard-card--sm`)
- Custom token variables: `--[category]-[name]` (e.g., `--color-bg-custom-surface`)

### When Adding New Files
- Add CSS imports to the appropriate `index.css` file (`base/index.css` or `custom/index.css`).
- Never import component CSS directly in a component file — always through the index.

## Rule 5: Component Patterns

### Size Variants
When a component has size variants, use the standard scale: `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`, `2xl`.
Implement as BEM modifiers: `.button--sm`, `.button--lg`.

### State Handling
Standard states: `default`, `hover`, `focus`, `active`, `disabled`.
- Hover: use `--*-hover` tokens when available, otherwise lighten/darken by one step.
- Disabled: use `--color-bg-disabled`, `--color-text-disabled`, `--color-border-disabled`. Add `cursor: not-allowed` and `pointer-events: none`.
- Focus: always apply focus ring (see Accessibility).

### Hierarchy Variants
For components with visual weight levels: `primary`, `secondary`, `tertiary`, `link`.
- Primary: `--color-bg-brand-solid` background, white text.
- Secondary: `--color-bg-primary` background, brand-colored border.
- Tertiary: transparent background, brand-colored text.
- Link: no background/border, brand-colored text with underline.

### Semantic Color Variants
For status-indicating components (alerts, badges, tags): `brand`, `gray`, `error`, `warning`, `success`.

## Rule 6: Responsive Design

- Build mobile-first. Default styles target mobile.
- Standard breakpoints:
  ```css
  /* Tablet */
  @media (min-width: 768px) { }
  /* Desktop */
  @media (min-width: 1024px) { }
  /* Wide desktop */
  @media (min-width: 1280px) { }
  ```
- Use container tokens for max-width: `var(--container-max-width)` with `var(--container-padding-desktop)` / `var(--container-padding-mobile)`.
- Limit paragraph width with `max-width: var(--width-paragraph-max)` for readability.
- Test layouts at 320px, 768px, 1024px, and 1440px widths.

## Rule 7: Performance

- Prefer CSS custom properties over Sass/Less variables for runtime theming.
- Use `transition` on specific properties, never `transition: all`.
- Avoid `!important` — it breaks the token cascade. If needed, fix the specificity instead.
- Prefer `gap` over margin-based spacing in flex/grid layouts.
- Use `will-change` sparingly and only on elements that actually animate.

## Rule 8: Code Review Checklist

Before completing any frontend task, verify:

- [ ] No hardcoded colors — all colors use semantic tokens
- [ ] No hardcoded spacing — all spacing uses spacing tokens
- [ ] No hardcoded border-radius — all radii use radius tokens
- [ ] No hardcoded typography — all fonts use typography tokens
- [ ] No hardcoded shadows — all shadows use shadow tokens
- [ ] Dark mode works (semantic tokens used throughout)
- [ ] Focus styles are visible on all interactive elements
- [ ] All images have alt text
- [ ] All form inputs have labels
- [ ] Icon-only buttons have aria-label
- [ ] Touch targets are at least 44x44px
- [ ] Animations respect prefers-reduced-motion
- [ ] Component renders correctly at 320px and 1440px
- [ ] New files are in the correct directory (base/ vs custom/)
- [ ] CSS imports are added to the appropriate index.css
- [ ] No `!important` usage
- [ ] No `outline: none` without an alternative focus indicator
